critique: This document establishes and modifies the membership of the Air Coordinating Committee. It involves multiple government agencies, including State, Army, Navy, Air Force, Treasury, Post Office, Commerce Departments, and the Civil Aeronautics Board. The President retains the power to name the Chairman of the Committee. The order supersedes previous executive orders related to the committee's membership. There is no direct impact on immigration, civil liberties, or social inclusion. The economic impact is neutral. The federal government maintains control over the committee. The ideological tilt is neutral.
